    "description": "AIIMS, one of India's leading organizations, is hiring a Senior Doctor for our Meerut operations. We offer a competitive salary package along with world-class benefits.\n\nAbout AIIMS:\nAIIMS is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Provide high-quality patient care and maintain patient records\n• Maintain accurate clinical documentation in electronic health records\n• Conduct routine health assessments and screenings\n• Collaborate with pharmaceutical representatives and medical suppliers\n• Respond to medical emergencies and provide immediate care\n• Administer medications and treatments as prescribed\n• Monitor patient progress and adjust treatment plans accordingly\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Arch / M.Arch from recognized institution\n• 3-6 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Medical Coding\n• Proficiency in ICD-10\n• Proficiency in Clinical Documentation\n• Proficiency in Medical Ethics\n• Proficiency in HIPAA Compliance\n• Proficiency in Health Informatics\n• Proficiency in EMR/EHR\n• Proficiency in BLS/ACLS\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Life and accident insurance\n• Maternity and paternity leave\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Salary Range: 7 LPA - 15 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Meerut, Uttar Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with AIIMS!",
